name: Baked Sesame Chicken Wings
author: Josh Nelson
summary: An excellent baked sesame chicken wing recipe. Nothing fried or breaded here!
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Spray a 9x13-inch baking pan with cooking spray
Place frozen chicken wings, skin side-down, in the prepared pan
Combine soy sauce, water, and sugar in a bowl; pour sauce over chicken
Bake in the preheated oven for 30 minutes
Remove from the oven, turn wings, and sprinkle with sesame seeds
Return to the oven and bake until no longer pink at the bone and the juices run clear, about 30 minutes more
An instant-read thermometer inserted near the bone should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C)
